<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08204</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REDEFINING THE CRIME OF GAME-FIXING AND PRESCRIBING STIFFER PENALTIES THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Redefining The Crime Of Game - Fixing And Prescribing Stiffer Penalties Therefor</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Includes the act of point-shaving and game machinations as forms of game-fixing; Prescribes stiffer penalties of imprisonment from three (3) years to twelve (12) years and a fine of not less than One million (P1,000,000.00) to Five million (P5,000,000.00) pesos on the acts of game-fixing; Exempts from prosecution or punishment  any person who voluntarily discloses, testifies, or assist in the prosecution of any offenses of game-fixing.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>PINEDA, ENRICO A., BELMONTE, RICARDO &quot;RJ&quot; JR. T., SALO, RON P., MONTORO, TEODORO &quot;TED&quot; G., SALON, ORESTES T., LOPEZ, MANUEL LUIS T., LOPEZ, BENHUR JR. B., BERTIZ, ANICETO &quot;JOHN&quot; III D., BELARO, SALVADOR JR. B., LACSON, VIRGILIO S., UYBARRETA, CARLOS ROMAN, ESTRELLA, CONRADO III M., PACQUIAO, ROGELIO &quot;RUEL&quot; D., MANGAOANG, ALLEN JESSE C., ROMERO, MICHAEL ODYLON L., Ph.D., ROA-PUNO, CHIQUI, LAOGAN, DENNIS C., SIAO, FREDERICK W., BAGATSING, CRISTAL L., ORTEGA, PABLO, TEVES, ARNOLFO JR. A., SAMBAR, MARK AERON H., NOGRALES, JERICHO JONAS B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-09-10</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>AUTHORS(Final/Third Reading) :</td></tr><tr><td width='%33'>1. Pineda</td><td width='33%'>2. Belmonte (R.)</td><tr><td width='%33'>3. Salo</td><td width='33%'>4. Montoro</td><tr><td width='%33'>5. Salon</td><td width='33%'>6. Lopez (M.L.)</td><tr><td width='%33'>7. Lopez (B.)</td><td width='33%'>8. Bertiz</td><tr><td width='%33'>9. Belaro</td><td width='33%'>10. Lacson</td><tr><td wid